<li><a href="1996#11january1996">11 January 1996</a></li>
<li><a href="1996#1january1996">1 January 1996</a></li>
</ul><h2 id="12december1996">Update 783G # Date 12 December 1996</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 38 - CHILD SUPPORT - Child support paydays. See guideline 38.13000.</p>
<p>Child support paydays and affected family payment for 1997.</p>
<h2>Update 782G # Date 12 December 1996</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 12 - NEWSTART - Vocational training courses and Labour Market programs. See guidelines 12.2300 to 12.2377.</p>
<p>Newstart allowance to replace job search allowance. Some other changes to the voluntary work provisions in line with the 20 September changes and some policy clarification on the allowable activities self employment development and group co-operative enterprises.</p>
<h2>Update 781G # Date 12 December 1996</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 17 - FAMILY PAYMENT - Notifiable events - change in employment. See guideline 17.9102.</p>
<p>Clarification of the meaning of change jobs as a notifiable event.</p>
<h2>Update 780G # Date 12 December 1996</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 42 - PORTABILITY AND COMPARABLE FOREIGN PAYMENTS - Comparable foreign payments - amended addresses for overseas social security authorities. See guideline 42.2331.</p>
<p>Amended addresses for overseas social security authorities (Uruguay, Denmark, Iceland, Germany, El Salvador, France and Finland).</p>
<h2>Update 779G # Date 12 December 1996</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 17 - FAMILY PAYMENT - Employer Provided Benefits - School Fees. See guidelines 17.7640 to 17.7641.</p>
<p>Clarification of the definition of a school fees benefit.</p>
<h2 id="1december1996">Update 919G # Date 1 December 1996</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 26 - EDUCATION AND EDUCATION PAYMENTS - Employment and Education Payments. See guidelines 26.4400 to 26.6302.</p>
<p>Provides details of: eligibility for partner allowance, newstart mature age allowance; changes to qualifying period from registration with the Commonwealth Employment Service to receipt of income support payments; and current newstart allowance/youth training allowance, education entry payment entitlements.</p>
<h2>Update 918G # Date 1 December 1996</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 26 - EDUCATION AND EDUCATION PAYMENTS - Employment and Education Payments. See guidelines 26.000 to 26.1701.</p>
<p>Provides details of: eligibility for partner allowance, newstart mature age allowance; changes to qualifying period from registration with the Commonwealth Employment Service to receipt of income support payments; and current newstart allowance/youth training allowance, education entry payment entitlements.</p>
<h2 id="28november1996">Update 778G # Date 28 November 1996</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 12 - NEWSTART - Part l: Continuation Forms (Form SU19) - Part M: General Reviews. See guidelines 12.5340 to 12.17903.</p>
<p>Newstart allowance to replace job search allowance.</p>
<h2>Update 777G # Date 28 November 1996</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 12 - NEWSTART - Part B: Activity Test &amp; Part D: Allowable not payable. See guidelines 12.4000 to 12.5310.</p>
<p>Newstart allowance to replace job search allowance.</p>
<h2>Update 776G # Date 28 November 1996</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 12 - NEWSTART - Vocational training courses and labour market programs.</p>
<p>Guidelines 12.2600 to 12.2614 have been deleted because newstart allowance has replaced job search allowance.</p>
<h2>Update 775G # Date 28 November 1996</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 12 - NEWSTART - Part A: Basic Qualifications &amp; Part B: Activity Test. See guidelines 12.700 to 12.2003.</p>
<p>Newstart allowance to replace job search allowance.</p>
<h2>Update 774G # Date 28 November 1996</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 23 - ADDITIONAL PAYMENTS - RENT ASSISTANCE, PHARMACEUTICAL ALLOWANCE, TELEPHONE ALLOWANCE, REMOTE AREA ALLOWANCE - Clarify the meaning of rent paid as 'paid or payable' and correct a couple of typing errors. See guidelines 23.150 to 23.155 and 23.300 to 23.301.</p>
<p>Clarify the meaning of rent paid as 'paid or payable' and correct a couple of typing errors.</p>
<h2>Update 772G to 773G # Date 28 November 1996</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 2 - METHODS OF PAYMENT AND TAXATION &amp; CHAPTER 15 - SPECIAL BENEFIT - Stopping of double payments. See guidelines 2.3000 to 2.3008 and 15.3100 to 15.3103. (deleted in issue 1330G)</p>
<p>Changes made to reflect National Instruction CB960167 - Transfers from period-based to payday-based payments.</p>
<h2 id="31october1996">Update 767G to 771G # Date 31 October 1996</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 38 - CHILD SUPPORT - Part I of chapter 27 (maintenance income test) is now included in chapter 38 as Part K. Part K and Part L of chapter 38 are now Part L and Part M. See guidelines 38.1200, 38.4300 to 38.4304, 38.4800 to 38.4811, 38.6200 to 38.6203, and 38.9800 to 38.13000.</p>
<p>Part I of chapter 27 (maintenance income test) is now included in chapter 38 as Part K. Part K and Part L of chapter 38 are now Part L and Part M. Minor changes such as corrections to cross references have also been made.</p>
<h2>Update 766G # Date 31 October 1996</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 7 - FAMILY PAYMENT - Notification of discharge from an approved care organisation. See guidelines 17.16200 to 17.16202.</p>
<p>The notification period for Family Payment under Sections 872 and 873 has been changed from 14 days to 21 days.</p>
<h2>Update 765G # Date 31 October 1996</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 7 - FAMILY PAYMENT - Suspension/cancellation. See guidelines 17.12020 to 17.12025.</p>
<p>The notification period for Family Payment under Sections 872 and 873 has been changed from 14 days to 21 days.</p>
<h2>Update 764G # Date 31 October 1996</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 7 - FAMILY PAYMENT - Family payment reassessments. See guidelines 17.7800 to 17.782302.</p>
<p>The notification period for Family Payment under Sections 872 and 873 has been changed from 14 days to 21 days.</p>
<h2>Update 763G # Date 31 October 1996</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 7 - FAMILY PAYMENT - Claim procedures. See guidelines 17.1000 to 17.1003.</p>
<p>The notification period for family payment under sections 872 and 873 has been changed from 14 days to 21 days.</p>
<h2>Update 762G # Date 31 October 1996</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 7 - FAMILY PAYMENT - Changes to student income and dependency during the income year. See guideline 17.3233.</p>
<p>The notification period for family payment under sections 872 and 873 has been changed from 14 days to 21 days.</p>
<h2 id="17october1996">Update 761G # Date 17 October 1996</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 1 - GENERAL PROCEDURES inc.TAX FILE NUMBER EXEMPTIONS - Claim treated as claim for another social security payment. See guidelines 1.1400 to 1.1408 and 1.1440 to 1.1441.</p>
<p>The guidelines have been amended to advise that claims for compensation under State legislation cannot be accepted as a claim for social security payment.</p>
<h2>Update 760G # Date 17 October 1996</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 2 - METHODS OF PAYMENT AND TAXATION - Eligibility for Urgent Cheque Payment. See guidelines 2.3600 to 2.3643.</p>
<p>The change clarifies the meaning of severe financial hardship for the purposes of deciding whether to issue an urgent payment.</p>
<h2>Update 758 &amp; 759G # Date 17 October 1996</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 24 - BEREAVEMENT PAYMENTS - Lump sum bereavement payments. See guidelines 24.1600 to 24.2201 and 24.6300 to 24.6541.</p>
<p>These changes provide more up to date examples of lump sum bereavement payment calculations.</p>
<h2 id="3october1996">Update 757G # Date 3 October 1996</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 40 - DISABILITY WAGE SUPPLEMENT - Cross reference to youth rates at guideline 6.150. See guideline 40.102.</p>
<p>Part of splitting of old chapter 27. Youth rates for disability support pension (DSP) and disability wage supplement (DWS) have been moved to guideline 6.150.</p>
<h2>Update 756G # Date 3 October 1996</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 6 - DISABILITY SUPPORT PENSION - Transfer of youth rates from chapter 27 to guideline 6.150. See guidelines 6.150 to 6.182.</p>
<p>Part of splitting of old chapter 27. Youth rates for disability support pension (DSP) and disability wage supplement (DWS) have been moved to guideline 6.150.</p>
<h2>Update 755G # Date 3 October 1996</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 17 - FAMILY PAYMENT - Dependant child under 16. See guidelines 17.3110 to 17.3120.</p>
<p>Clarification of dependancy of a child under five who's income is over the income limit.</p>
<h2>Update 754G # Date 3 October 1996</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 5 - AGE PENSION - Qualifying age for women - Increment for increase should be two yearly. See guidelines 5.010 to 5.011.</p>
<p>The qualifying age is increased each 24 months not 18 months.</p>
<h2>Update 753G # Date 3 October 1996</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 14 - SICKNESS ALLOWANCE See guidelines 14.000 to 14.6202.</p>
<p>This chapter has been rewritten taking into account the effect of the 'no more transfers from JSA' initiative which was implemented in March 1996.</p>
<h2>Update 752G # Date 3 October 1996</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 18 - CHILD DISABILITY ALLOWANCE - Recovery of Child Disability Allowance (CDA) overpayments to parents/guardians of children who have transferred to Disability Wage Supplement. See guidelines 18.3400 to 18.3403.</p>
<p>Child Disability Allowance (CDA) paid to a parent/guardian after grant of DWS is a recoverable overpayment. Amendment to correct current Guide reference.</p>
<h2 id="19september1996">Update 751G # Date 19 September 1996</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 47 - DROUGHT RELIEF PAYMENTS - Date of commencement and date of effect of certificate. See guidelines 47.4000 to 47.4004.</p>
<p>Provision of drought declaration dates.</p>
<h2>Update 750G # Date 19 September 1996</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 47 - DROUGHT RELIEF PAYMENTS - Cessation of drought exceptional circumstances. See guidelines 47.10000 to 47.10004.</p>
<p>Provision of drought revocation dates.</p>
<h2>Update 749G # Date 19 September 1996</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 1 - GENERAL PROCEDURES inc TAX FILE NUMBER EXEMPTION - Conditions of payment for special benefit. See guidelines 1.8000 to 1.8008.</p>
<p>Clarification of which available funds test to use in extended eligibility temporary entry permit (EETEP) cases.</p>
<h2>Update 748G # Date 19 September 1996</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 13 - FARM HOUSEHOLD SUPPORT - Re-establishment grant. See guidelines 13.21000 to 13.21001.</p>
<p>Correction to conditions under which grant is paid.</p>
<h2>Update 747G # Date 19 September 1996</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 15 - SPECIAL BENEFIT - Assurances of support. See guidelines 15.1300 to 15.1301.</p>
<p>Change of cross reference to rate payable.</p>
<h2>Update 746G # Date 19 September 1996</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 41 - PARENTING ALLOWANCE - Member of a couple. See guidelines 41N.1010 to 41N.1013.</p>
<p>Clarification of definition of member of a couple.</p>
<h2>Update 745G # Date 19 September 1996</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 12 - NEWSTART - Payment of job search allowance/newstart allowance for three weeks from date of commencement of AUSTUDY/ABSTUDY course. See guidelines 12.5320 to 12.5330.</p>
<p>The current wording in the guide provides an incorrect cancellation reason when a customer has returned to an AUSTUDY approved course. By using this code the customer does not receive their education entry payment.</p>
<h2 id="5september1996">Update 744G # Date 5 September 1996</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 1 - GENERAL PROCEDURES inc TAX FILE NUMBER EXEMPTIONS - Claim treated as claim for another social security payment - inclusion of parenting allowance. See guidelines 1.1430 to 1.1434.</p>
<p>A claim for double orphan pension can be backdated to the date of an earlier claim for family payment, CDA and parenting allowance.</p>
<h2>Update 743G # Date 5 September 1996</h2>
