<h2>Update 708G # Date 25 July 1996</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 8 - CARER PENSION - Carer pension - residence of carer - removal of adjacent rule. See guidelines 8.2500 to 8.2503.</p>
<p>From 1 July 1996, there is no longer a requirement that the carer live in the same home as, or an adjacent home to, the caree to receive carer pension. Carers who live some distance away from the caree will be eligible for carer pension, as long as the care requirements are met.</p>
