<h2>Update 623G # Date 18 April 1996</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 42 - PORTABILITY AND COMPARABLE FOREIGN PAYMENTS - Claiming pension from a non-comparable foreign payment country. See guidelines 42.2330 to 42.2340.</p>
<p>The guidelines update address for non-comparable foreign payment (CFP) countries and a new guideline on embargoing arrears from CFP countries.</p>
<h2>Update 622G # Date 18 April 1996</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 27 - DETERMINING RATES OF PAYMENT - Earnings Credit Scheme for allowances.</p>
<p>The amendments provide information on the changes to the Earnings Credit Scheme for allowance recipients that were announced in the 1995/96 Budget. From 20 March 1996, the maximum amount of Earnings Credit that can be offset against earnings is $100.00 a fortnight; the rate of accrual is the difference between a customer's ordinary income (OI) and the OI free area, and the earnings credit cannot be offset against income earned after a person ceased to qualify for allowance.</p>
<h2>Update 621G # Date 18 April 1996</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 9 - SOLE PARENT PENSION - Selective review at 8 &amp; 12 weeks after grant. See guidelines 9.1300 to 9.1301.</p>
<p>Increase 8 &amp; 12 week sole parent pension review targets from 50% to 70%.</p>
