<h2 id="2april1996">Update 633G # Date 2 April 1996</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 27 - DETERMINING RATES OF PAYMENT - Conversion of sterling to Australian dollars.</p>
<p>Social security sets a new UK exchange rate if the average of the Commonwealth Bank's on demand airmail buying rate over a ten day monitoring period varies by 2.5% or more when compared to the Department's exchange rate.</p>
<h2 id="21march1996">Update 605G # Date 21 March 1996</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 27 - DETERMING RATES OF PAYMENT - Community based care and other exempt assets subsections.</p>
<p>Complete restructure of exempt assets subsections of Part G: Assessment of Assets. New Community based care changes - changes to circumstances where rent assistance may be payable to homeowners. Changed references to nursing homes to 'in a care situation' as stated in subsection 13.9 of the Act, which includes both nursing homes and a substantial level of care in a private residence. Incorporation of considerable new material on other exempt assets including special residences, granny flats, sale-leaseback residences and company owned residences.</p>
