<h2>Update 608G # Date 20 March 1996</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 23 - ADDITIONAL PAYMENTS - RENT ASSISTANCE, PHARMACEUTICAL ALLOWANCE, TELEPHONE ALLOWANCE, REMOTE AREA ALLOWANCE - 1995/96 budget changes to rent assistance. See guidelines 23.100 to 23.601.</p>
<p>The rent assistance (RA) changes announced in the 1995/96 Budget take effect from 20 March 1996. In addition to the cost of living increase, all rent thresholds increased by an extra $5.00 a fortnight, as too the maximum rates of RA for families with children. In addition, a strategy has been introduced to phase out the RA savings provisions more quickly.</p>
<p>Other changes permit RA to be paid to people 'in a care situation'.</p>
<p>New policy direction is given in relation to RA during certain periods of temporary accommodation, and outline treatment of housing assistance in lieu of cash maintenance.</p>
