<h2>Update 583G # Date 7 March 1996</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 8 - CARER PENSION - Carer pension - March 1996 changes. See guidelines 8.000 to 8.5300.</p>
<p>Amendments to reflect two changes to legislation with effect from 21 March 1996 to:</p>
<ul><li>extend eligibility for carer pension to include carers of severely handicapped people who are not income support recipients, subject to the care receiver having income and assets below the levels at which a person with one dependent child can receive minimum family payment (currently taxable income below $63,766 pa and assets below $584,500). The carer will still need to meet the pension income and assets tests;</li>
<li>continue payment of carer pension for 14 weeks when the person being cared for is permanently institutionalised.</li>
</ul><p>Also, chapter re-written to provide more guidance on some policy issues.</p>
