<h2>Update 549G # Date 25 January 1996</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 47 - DROUGHT RELIEF PAYMENTS - Links with other payments. See guidelines 47.14000 to 47.14013.</p>
<p>Amendments to guidelines to reflect changes to legislation.</p>
<h2>Update 548G # Date 25 January 1996</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 18 - CHILD DISABILITY ALLOWANCE - Child disability allowance eligibility will change as at 1 January 1996. See guidelines 18.000 to 18.7400.</p>
<p>Child disability allowance (CDA) eligibility will change as at 1 January 1996. CDA can be paid for a child up until the child turns 22 instead of 25. CDA forms (Form SC5 - CDA Claim Form) and (Form SC202 - CDA Determination of Claim/Review) have changed. They both now have 3 parts (A, B &amp; C) instead of 2. Whole chapter has been reissued.</p>
<h2 id="11january1996">Update 547G # Date 11 January 1996</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 27 - DETERMINING RATES OF PAYMENT - new examples of rate calculations following amalgamation of basic family payment (BFP) and additional family payment (AFP). See guidelines 27.28000 to 27.30401.</p>
<p>Part N - examples of family payment calculations and part O - examples of lump sum child related bereavement payment calculations - rewritten.</p>
<h2>Update 546G # Date 11 January 1996</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 14 - SICKNESS ALLOWANCE - This amendment clarifies the existing guideline. Where a client's employment has not been terminated and a payment of annual leave is made, then a loss of income has not occurred. See guidelines 17.7000 to 17.7004.</p>
<h2 id="1january1996">Update 681G # Date 1 January 1996</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 17 - FAMILY PAYMENT - Payment of family payment for over 16s. See guidelines 17.3130 to 17.3132.</p>
<p>Clarification of the definition of secondary studies.</p>
